Path: godot/classes/class_capsulemesh.rst
Summary: A class representing a capsule-shaped primitive mesh used in 3D modeling within Godot Engine.

Inherits: PrimitiveMesh < Mesh < Resource < RefCounted < Object
Class representing a capsule-shaped primitive mesh. Used to create 3D shapes with rounded ends and cylindrical middle section. Commonly used for character collision shapes and simple 3D models.
---CHUNK---
Document: CapsuleMesh
Path: godot/classes/class_capsulemesh.rst
Summary: Represents a capsule-shaped primitive mesh in 3D space.

Class representing a capsule-shaped PrimitiveMesh. A capsule mesh consists of a cylinder with hemispherical ends, commonly used for collision shapes and 3D modeling. This class inherits from PrimitiveMesh and provides methods for configuring capsule dimensions and subdivisions.
