Document: CapsuleMesh
Path: godot/classes/class_capsulemesh.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring the dimensions and detail of a CapsuleMesh in Godot.

height (float): Total height of the capsule mesh (including the hemispherical ends). Default: 2.0. Set/Get: set_height(value: float), get_height(). Note: The height of a capsule must be at least twice its radius. Otherwise, the capsule becomes a circle. If the height is less than twice the radius, the properties adjust to a valid value.

radial_segments (int): Number of radial segments on the capsule mesh. Default: 64. Set/Get: set_radial_segments(value: int), get_radial_segments().

radius (float): Radius of the capsule mesh. Default: 0.5. Set/Get: set_radius(value: float), get_radius(). Note: The radius of a capsule cannot be greater than half of its height. Otherwise, the capsule becomes a circle. If the radius is greater than half the height, the properties adjust to a valid value.

rings (int): Number of rings along the height of the capsule. Default: 8. Set/Get: set_rings(value: int), get_rings().